The Master Key is more like an experienced player and/or speedrunner type of item. I myself like the Old Witch's Ring for the extra content it provides. text:
Happy to see Gura giving it a shot. 

I know a lot of people who love this game tend to be a bit too much, but i have a belief its in part of 2 kinds of players. The players who believe there is a right and wrong way to play the game, and the kind of person who wants others who want to genuinely guide others because there are a lot of things that the game refuses to explain and are easy to miss. I personally tend to become more of the 2nd but I have quelled that natural instinct since streamers are looking for how to play the game. Where as forums and the like are better places to give assistance to others who ask for it.

text: I do always find the focus on people playing it "wrong " weird. The game is pretty flexible, there are a huge number of viable ways to get through it, heavy armor, shields, fast rolls, parrying, magic, items, weapons, etc. And the all purpose fuck this button, jolly cooperation. Or just grinding. Boss fights can have tricks but you usually can just bryte force your way through (ceaseless discharge). text: @CuriosityMisledMe¬† I agree to an extent. The thing is, when I first got into soul's games, I mainly immersed myself in the YouTube space, talking about how the game is played. Even had a play through that I mimicked because I wanted to find some of the more obscure areas of the game and  follow the theory crafting others we doing at the time.
author: @hunterking87

text:
¬†@hunterking87¬† The only things in Dark Souls I can think of that you wouldn‚Äôt be able to naturally encounter is finding the Darkwraith Covenant, The Great Hollow/Ash Lake, a couple of quest lines, and the entrance to the DLC. Everything else can be found if you‚Äôre willing to take your time to think things through, along with reading item descriptions. 

Besides, you don‚Äôt need to find everything in the game on your first play through. Where‚Äôs the fun in exploration when you‚Äôre told exactly what to expect and what to do next by someone else? You may as well just hand them the controller at that point.
